{
    "problem": "Determine the value of $-1 + 2 + 3 + 4 - 5 - 6 - 7 - 8 - 9 + \\dots + 10000$, where the signs change after each perfect square.",
    "level": "Level 5",
    "type": "Intermediate Algebra",
    "solution": "We can express the sum as\n\\begin{align*}\n\\sum_{n = 1}^{100} (-1)^n \\sum_{k = (n - 1)^2 + 1}^{n^2} k &= \\sum_{n = 1}^{100} (-1)^n \\cdot \\frac{(n - 1)^2 + 1 + n^2}{2} \\cdot (2n - 1) \\\\\n&= \\sum_{n = 1}^{100} (-1)^n (2n^3 - 3n^ 2+ 3n - 1) \\\\\n&= \\sum_{n = 1}^{100} (-1)^n (n^3 + (n - 1)^3) \\\\\n&= -0^3 - 1^3 + 1^3 + 2^3 - 2^3 - 3^3 + \\dots + 99^3 + 100^3 \\\\\n&= \\boxed{1000000}.\n\\end{align*}"
}